<HEADLINE> Italian PM Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Ramano Prodi
today tended his resignation of his centre-left government and
President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro asked him to stay in as a caretaker.
</P>
<P>
A presidential statement said the president has "reserved his
decision and asked the government in office to carry out routine
affairs."
</P>
<P>
Earlier today Prodi announced that he was going to resign
following the end of a debate in the Chamber of Deputies over the
17-month-old coalition's economic policy.
</P>
<P>
Prodi's decision followed his failure to persuade the far-left
Refounded Communists to back the government's budget cuts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
