<HEADLINE> Courier, Stark Advance to Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Third seed Jim Courier of
United States and defending champion Jonathan Stark ousted their
counterparts respectively to enter the Singapore Open tennis
quarter-finals on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Former world number one Courier, who won the China Open in
Beijing last week, downed Australian Michael Tebbutt 6-4, 7-6 (7-)
and his compatriot Stark dropped a set before stopping Slovakian
Jiri Novak 6-3, 3-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Both the Americans must overcome difficult Swedish opponents
for a place in the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
Four-time Grand Slam champion Courier takes on fifth seed
Thomas Johansson, who downed Marcos Ondruska of South Africa 6-4,
6-4 and Stark plays seventh seed Magnus Gustafsson, who fought
hard with German Martin Sinner 7-6 (7-4), 4-6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The other quarterfinals pit second-seed Marcelo Rios of Chile
against Nicolas Kiefer of Germany and Czech Martin Damm against
Mikael Tillstrom of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
In the doubles, top seed India's Leander Paes and Mahesh
Bhupathi downed Marcos Ondruska and Grant Stafford of South Africa
6-4, 3-6, 6-3 to set up a last-four date with Mikael Tillstrom and
Niklas Kulti of Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The Swedes defeat David Wheaton of the United States and Chris
Wilkinson of Britain 5-7, 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (7-3) in a quarterfinal
rally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
