<HEADLINE> Germany to Host World Bank Conference on Southern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 9 (Xinhua) -- A World Bank investment conference
on southern Africa is due to be held in the southern German city
of Stuttgart on November 20-21, the German Daimler-Benz AG, which
will play host to the gathering, announced today.
</P>
<P>
World Bank President James Wolfensohn, political leaders from
the African region and German business leaders are expected to
attend the conference to discuss investment opportunities in
southern Africa, the company said.
</P>
<P>
Daimler-Benz chief Juergen Schrempp, who is also chairman of
the Southern Africa Initiative of German Industry, is currently on
a visit to the region to prepare for the meeting.
</P>
<P>
He was quoted by company sources as saying that German business
had to learn more about Africa. "This region is offering us
enormous development potential," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
