<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe, Japan to Discuss Economic Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Investment Center
(ZIC) today said it will hold a workshop next Monday on
Zimbabwean-Japanese economic relations and privatization in
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
A high powered business delegation from Japan will attend the
meeting, the ZIC said.
</P>
<P>
"The businessmen will be dispatched by the Japanese government
to study the industrial, economic and investment climate in
Zimbabwe through discussions with relevant officials from the
private and public sectors," said ZIC Public Relations Manager
Bekithemba Mhlanga.
</P>
<P>
He said the business delegation will seek information on
business opportunities in Zimbabwe with a special focus on
manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
Tourism, mining, transport and construction are other areas of
interest, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The delegation is hoping to get answers on enquiries made on
the role of the private sector in the privatization process,
monetary and fiscal policy," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
