<HEADLINE> Croatia, China Should Enhance Relations: Tudjman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Croatian President Franjo Tudjman
said here today that his country hoped to further expand its
cooperative ties with China in the political, economic and
cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when meeting with Chinese Vice Foreign
Minister Zhang Deguang at his presidential residence.
</P>
<P>
Tudjman highly valued the important role China plays in the
international affairs and wished China to make greater
contributions to promoting peace and stability in the former
Yugoslav region.
</P>
<P>
After congratulating once again the Chinese government's
resumption of the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, Tudjman
hoped China could realize the reunification of motherland
according to the "One Country, Two Systems" model as early as
possible.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice minister spoke highly of the peaceful foreign
policy that the Balkan country pursues.
</P>
<P>
China supports Croatia's efforts in safeguarding its
independence, sovereignty and territorial integrity, Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Chinese vice minister also met with Croatian
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Mate Granic and Deputy
Foreign Minister Ivo Banader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
