<HEADLINE> UK Insurers Keen to Play Constructive Role in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Leading British insurance firms
will be exhibiting at the Indo-British Partnership's "Towards
2000" in New Delhi next week, the Department of Trade and Industry
(DTI) announced today.
</P>
<P>
The firms including the Prudential, Lloyds, Standard Life and
Eagle Star are combining to recreate a Lime Street Coffee House
where the insurance business began in the City of London in the
early 17th century.
</P>
<P>
They will also demonstrate their individual expertise and
state-of-the art technology which makes Britain a world leader in
insurance in the number of newly created and well-paid jobs in the
Indian insurance sector can be expected, according to the DTI.
</P>
<P>
The insurance companies are but one group among some 130
leading British companies participating in the "Towards 2000"
exhibition being held from 14-18 October in New Delhi.
</P>
<P>
The DTI quoted Warwick Morris, head of trade promotion and
investment in New Delhi, as saying, "As India increasingly sees
the need to liberalize its economy in order to become a major
global player..., British insurance companies can, and will, make
a tremendous contribution to the development of this key sector
and to the Indian economy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
