<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fighting with Mixed Claims Reported in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Heavy fighting is reported to
have broken out last night between the forces of Hussein Mohamed
Aidid and those of the Rahanwein Resistance Army (RRA) in
Somalia's southwestern town of Baidoa and its surrounding areas.
</P>
<P>
According to sources available here today, the fighting
which continued until mid day today started after dozens of
heavily armed militiamen from the RRA had entered the town
sneaking through the front defense positions of Hussein Aidid's
men late last night and attacked the militia quarters of Hussein
Aidid's men inside the town.
</P>
<P>
The sources from the RRA in Mogadishu said their forces
defeated Hussein aidid's men, inflicting them heavy losses during
the fighting and took control of Baidoa Town, 245 km southwest of
Mogadishu early this morning.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the RRA said their forces are currently
fighting Hussein Aidid's men in Manyo Fuulka Village, 12km south
of Baidoa. However, the spokesman declined to mention any
casualty figures from either side.
</P>
<P>
There's no official word from Hussein Aidid's side over the
fighting as yet. Nevertheless, a spokesman for Hussein Aidid who
declined his name has characterized the fighting as a little
skirmish carried out by what he called bandits.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that their forces have driven
the RRA fighters out of Baidoa Town and its surrounding areas in
the early hours of today. The spokesman also said that Baidoa is
now calm under the full control of Hussein Aidid's forces.
</P>
</TEXT>
