<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Gambia Tourist Plane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, October 9 (Xinhua)-- A tourist charter plane from
Spain crashed in the west African state of Gambia Thursday,
killing eight of the nine people on board, said a report
reaching here from Gambia's capital Banjul.
</P>
<P>
"Out of the nine people on board one survived," the Gambian
Civil Aviation Authority said in a statement, after the plane
crashed on the approaches to the airport in the capital Banjul.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the plane had seven passengers and two crew
on board.
</P>
<P>
Seven of the dead were reported to be German tourists.
</P>
<P>
The former British colony of Gambia, which is on Africa's
Atlantic coast, is popular with tourists from western Europe.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the plane crashed at Kebujeh, about three km
from the airport. 
</P>
</TEXT>
