<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 7-nation War Games Kick Off in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The joint war games "Bright Star
97" kicked off today with the participation of forces from Egypt,
the United States, Finland, France, Italy, the United Arab
Emirates and Kuwait, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Military observers from 20 more countries are also taking part
in the exercises which will last until October 31, MENA said. But
it customarily did not mention where exactly the exercises were
held in Egypt.
</P>
<P>
The British and Egyptian forces started the maneuvers by
staging survival exercises and combat training that involves
airborne and land forces.
</P>
<P>
During October 13-16, Italy will begin drilling in setting up
emergency humanitarian aid center in time of natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
"Bright Star 97" will unfold its major part on October 23-31
with different arms of the services and troops from all the seven
countries taking part to hone up various combating skills.
</P>
<P>
The exercises started as early as 1981 and are being held once
every two years. They initially involved merely Egypt and the
U.S. until forces from other countries began to join in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
