<HEADLINE> Arab Children Call for World Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Arab children today directed a
call for peace to all world leaders and to U.N. Secretary General
Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
The call was made by representatives of the Arab children to
the second Arab forum for distinguished children held at the Arab
League headquarters here on the occasion of the Arab Child Day.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 90 children from 12 Arab countries, aging 12-18,
attended the forum under the theme "Children, the best investment
for the future," according to Egypt's Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The children told the forum that they are against "war,
destruction, treason and assassination of innocence," stressing
the right of the world children to live in peace and
security. They vowed to fight for their rights and against the
spread of conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's first lady Suzan Mubarak awarded the Arab House Medal
to the children at the annual gathering to honor their creativity.
</P>
<P>
In her opening address, Suzan Mubarak warned of the effect of
poverty, wars, political violence, terrorism and extremism on
children.
</P>
<P>
She said that the Arab education and health systems should be
reformed to serve the children's interests.
</P>
<P>
"The children should be allowed to enjoy their lives and their
freedom of thinking and creativity to build their
self-confidence," she added.
</P>
<P>
She also called for the adoption of a new Arab strategy to
encourage children to excel themselves and increase their sense of
nationality, which she said is "the best way to build a solid and
unified Arab nation."
</P>
<P>
Arab League Secretary General Esmat Abdul Meguid presented to
the first lady an Arab League shield in appreciation of her
efforts to serve childhood and motherhood causes. 
</P>
