<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 34 Sphinx Statues Discovered in Southern Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 9 (Xinhua) -- An Egyptian archeological team has
hit upon 34 sphinx statues along the Rams Road in the Upper
Egyptian city of Luxor, the site of ancient Egyptian rituals, the
Middle East News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Mohamad Al-Sagheer, director of Luxor and Upper Egyptian
Archeological Department who spearheaded the discovering team,
said some of the new statues date back to the age of King
Tutankhamen who ruled Egypt during 1361-52 BC.
</P>
<P>
Tutankhamen is known chiefly for his intact tomb discovered in
1922. During his reign, powerful advisers restored the traditional
religion and art style.
</P>
<P>
The fresh discovery has brought the number of sphinx statues
unearthed in the area to some 600, Sagheer said.
</P>
<P>
Studies estimate that about 1,200 sphinx statues exist within
an area of just a few square kilometers near Luxor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
