<HEADLINE> U.S. Extends Loan Repayments to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The United States
government today signed here with the government of Ethiopia a
bilateral debt agreement in a major move to alleviate
Ethiopia's debt burden.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the agreement is part
of the debt relief extended to Ethiopia by Paris Club creditors.
</P>
<P>
The report said, the debt agreement deal began when the
government of Ethiopia reached an agreement with Paris Club
creditor countries on January 24 this year to reduce and
reschedule Ethiopia's bilateral debts.
</P>
<P>
Under the terms of the new agreement, Ethiopia agrees to repay
the consolidated debt and the consolidated arrears it owes to the
U.S. in 48 consecutive semi-annual installments starting in the
year 2014 and ending in 2038 according to a specified schedule,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
Interest on the debt and arrears will be paid on a semi-annual
basis beginning in November this year, the report added. 
</P>
