<HEADLINE> French Socialist Party Regrets Prodi's Resignation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 9 (Xinhua) -- France's ruling Socialist Party
regretted the resignation presented today by Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi, and cautioned Italians against the rise of
the extreme-right in their country.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted Socialist Party First Secretary
Francois Hollande as saying that the action undertaken by the
government of Prodi over the past one year led Italy onto the
track of economic readjustment and national cohesion.
</P>
