<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Postal Services Need to Diversify: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian Postal
Corporation (TPC) has been advised to upgrade technology, provide
new services and develop the present business if it is to survive
the stiff competition.
</P>
<P>
Hairsh Bhatt, a charted information system engineer, told
participants in a workshop held in Dar es Salaam today that
diversification of services is the sole way out for TPC.
</P>
<P>
"You have to operate commercially, formulate better policies,
and provide quality and efficient services," he said.
</P>
<P>
Bhatt said alternative communications channels using
information technology (IT) are a real threat to the postal
services, addinging unless something is done, TPC's market share
in personal and business mail will be eroded in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Technologies such as Internet will not only have an impact on
postal services, but also on telephones, publishing and
advertising, Bhatt noted.
</P>
<P>
Internet, however, is not expected to replace all paper-based
documents although it is expected to undergo rapid expansion in
many countries in the coming five to ten years.
</P>
<P>
The information system engineer urged the TPC to buy
affordable personal computers which have an internet connection
and work like TV but disseminate information instantly in any
part of the world.
</P>
<P>
"TPC can open up communication centers in rural areas, using
these computers under its supervision thus meeting the clients'
needs and facilitating the development of the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
This will only be possible if TPC will review its policies,
operate commercially and invite potential investors who will be
attracted by a better trend of the company, Bhatt said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
