</P>
<P>
Iranian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has about 3,000
fighters. It is fighting to oust Israel's 1,200 soldiers and the
2,500 troops of the Israeli ally, South Lebanon Army from the
Israeli-occupied south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
It has killed nearly 200 Israeli soldiers in the South since
1985, when Israel set up a 1,000-square-kilometer "security zone"
there to prevent cross-border guerrilla raids. 
