consequences," Cohen said at a photo session with Israeli
President Erez Weizman at the Pentagon.
</P>
<P>
"We have taken measures to tighten (control over) the area
around which they seem intent on seeking to exploit on a very
quick and piecemeal basis," he said. But he did not elaborate what
measures the U.S. military had taken.
</P>
<P>
The Pentagon said on Wednesday the U.S. warplanes had recently
increased patrols over the two zones set in northern and southern
Iraq
</P>
<P>
The U.S. aircraft carrier Nimitz is now steaming toward the
Gulf ahead of schedule with more than 40 warplanes to help patrol
the no-fly zone in the southern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that Saddam Hussein continues to violate the no-fly
zones on a periodic basis... He is posing a risk to his pilots
whenever they start to challenge the no-fly zone," Cohen said.
</P>
<P>
Iran launched attack last week on bases of the Mujahideen
guerilla bases inside Iraq and Iraqi jet fighters rose to defend
the area, which was deemed by the United States as "violation"
of the no-fly zone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
