<HEADLINE> UK Base Interest Rates Stay Unchanged at 7% </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Britain's official interest rates
are to stay on hold at seven percent, Britain's central bank the
Bank of England's Monetary Policy Committee announced today.
</P>
<P>
The move will bring relief for millions of homebuyers and
businesses who have seen the base rate rise four times since the
general election in May.
</P>
<P>
The decision was as expected and came despite the fact that the
inflation rate is still above the government's 2.5 percent target.
</P>
<P>
But industry has pointed to figures showing that economic
growth is still sluggish, reducing fears of inflation.
</P>
<P>
However, Germany and France shocked global markets by raising
key rates, followed immediately by several other European
countries.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Bundesbank raised its repo rate to 3.3 percent from
3.0 percent today and the Bank of France followed suit and lifted
its intervention rate to 3.3 percent from 3.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that today's central bank fiscal signals marked
the first co-ordinated European interest rate action toward
European economic and monetary union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
