<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Take Part in "World Telefood" Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus will participate in
"World Telefood," the first global television appeal by the Food
and Agriculture Organization (FAO) to the general public to raise
funds for food security projects and activities.
</P>
<P>
This was announced here today by Minister of Agriculture,
Natural Resources and Environment Costas Petrides in his speech on
the occasion of the World Food Day.
</P>
<P>
The minister called on all Cypriots to contribute to Telefood,
which sets the target for Cyprus at 100,000 Cyprus pounds (about
200,000 U.S. dollars). The Telefood program will take place
between October 17-19.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent FAO report, of FAO's 174 member-states,
86 face food insufficiency problems, while 800 million adults and
200 million children under the age of five worldwide do not have
access to adequate food.
</P>
<P>
In his message today, Amor Ben Romdhane, FAO's representative
in Cyprus, said "World Telefood" consists of a series of
television events organized simultaneously at national level in
participating countries.
</P>
<P>
The initiative has two major objectives: to raise awareness
and mobilize resources in order to achieve food for all, Romdhane
said. 
</P>
