<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Jobless Rate Remains Unchanged in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Canada's jobless rate remained
at 9 percent in September, unchanged for the third consecutive
month, Statistics Canada reported today.
</P>
<P>
Canada's overall employment edged up slightly in the month,
bringing the gain, which started from February, to 293,000, the
federal statistics agency said.
</P>
<P>
September saw more full-time employment with a growth of 72,000
and fewer part-time jobs with a fall of 56,000, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
In the month, employment in the private sector increased by
17,000, with a gain of 44,000 in employees and a decline of 27,000
in self-employment. The employment in the public sector remained
at the same level.
</P>
<P>
Since February this year, the country's private sector has
generated 331,000 jobs, with self-employment accounting for a
quarter of this growth.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, public sector employment has trended downwards,
with a loss of 38,000 jobs over the same period.
</P>
<P>
In September, most industries showed little employment change,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
While there was employment growth in the mining, quarrying and
oil well industry, this gain was partly offset by a loss in
agriculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
