<DOCNO> XIE19971010.0073 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNCTAD Governing Board to Hold Annual Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Trade and Development Board
of the United Nations Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD)
will hold its annual session here next week.
</P>
<P>
The UNCTAD Trade and Development Board is the organization's
highest executive body between the quadrennial ministerial
conferences. During the session on October 13-24, discussions will
focus on the broad issues of economic interdependence and
globalization, and their impact on developing countries, notably,
their socio-economic development and competitiveness, according to
a UNCTAD press release. The main specific agenda items relate to
Africa and the Least Developed Countries (LDCs).
</P>
<P>
The board will also be informed about a four-day meeting to be
held in November 1998 in Lyon, France, with the aim of launching
"Partnerships for Development" in specific areas of the UNCTAD's
work, between non-governmental organizations (NGOs), the business
community, and governments.
F-  Of the UNCTAD's 188 members, 144 are members of the Trade and
Development Board. 
</P>
</TEXT>
