<HEADLINE> Mugabe Calls for Regional Cooperation in Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 10 (Xinhua) --Zimbabwean President Robert
Mugabe today called on the Zimbabwe Military Academy (ZMA) to
embrace students from neighouring countries into its training
programs.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a pass out parade for 100 regular officer cadets of
the ZMA in Gweru, central Zimbabwe, Mugabe said the move will
foster mutual cooperation, trust and good neighbourliness within
the south African sub-region.
</P>
<P>
''This will act as the launch pad for the realization of our
cherished hope to create a peaceful family of southern African
states endowed with the virtue of a common cause in securing
collective security,'' said Mugabe.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need for young officers to observe key and
principal tenents of professional rectitude, discipline,
patriotism and loyalty to their country.
</P>
<P>
The president noted that some of the conflicts currently
ravaging the continent are products of undisciplined and
untrained soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he commended Zimbabwean defence forces for
acquitting themselves well rin peace-keeping and observer
missions in Mozambique, Somalia, Rwanda and Angola.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe willcontinue to support and participate in
peace-keeping operation in conflict areas, Mugabe said.
</P>
<P>
The 100 cadets, 87 males and 13 females, had finalizedd a 13
-month course in basic military training and tactics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
