<HEADLINE> New Digital Telecommunications Network Links Major Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- A digital telecommunications
network linking Beijing with Shanghai, Guangzhou and Nanjing, the
first of its kind linking major Chinese cities, entered operations
today.
</P>
<P>
The network will offer fax, data and video transmission
services, in addition to regular telephone service. The network
will feature excellent quality, high speed and large volume data
transmissions.
</P>
<P>
It will also offer tele-conferencing, long-distance medical
consulting and education services.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has also established digital telecommunications links
with Japan, the United States, the Republic of Korea, Singapore,
Germany, Hong Kong and Taiwan, and by the end of this year, will
be expanded to cover Great Britain, Australia, Macao, Finland and
Switzerland. 
</P>
