<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China To Launch Nationwide Financial Audit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The State Council, the Chinese
cabinet, today issued a circular ordering a nationwide
audit of taxation and pricing activities, as well as other types
of enterprise financial activities, during 1996 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
The audit will commence in October and will be completed prior
to the traditional Spring Festival which falls on January 28,
1998, according to the circular.
</P>
<P>
The audit will be focus on major contributors of value-added,
consumption and income taxes, as well as enterprises engaged in
tax refundable exports, financial institutions, and state-run
grain purchasing companies.
</P>
<P>
The audit will also cover enterprises operated by government
departments, administrative agencies suspected of collecting
illegal charges and levies, and governmental and nongovernmental
units suspected of mismanagement or tax evasion, as well as those
with large volumes of nonbudgeted funds.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials from enterprises and institutions found to
have engaged in illegal activities will be severely disciplined
and punished, with those found to have committed minor offenses
also being subject to court hearings.
</P>
<P>
The State will confiscate all funds collected illegally,
according to the circular. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
