<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Oil Company Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
met with W Allen, chairman and CEO of Phillips Petroleum Company
of the United States, and other members of the board of the
company here today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said the Chinese government welcomes and supports the
cooperation between US businesses and Chinese firms.
</P>
<P>
He said he is happy to see that Phillips is conducting
cooperation with its Chinese counterpart in oil projects in
Northwest China.
</P>
<P>
He told the US visitors that China is formulating policies to
help speed up the economic development in the remote northwest
part of China.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation project in Northwest China "demonstrates the
Phillips' confidence in China's economy and its insight in future
development," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president, who is expected to pay a state visit to
the US at the invitation of President Bill Clinton soon, expressed
the hope that the high-level exchange of visits would help
increase mutual understanding between the people of the two
countries and promote the economic cooperation between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
Allen said he is looking forward to Jiang's state visit to the
US, which is important for further improvement and development of
US-China relations.
</P>
<P>
He said that his company has built up "satisfactory"
cooperation ties with Chinese companies over the past 20 years and
more. He added that China's economic growth is important to his
company.
</P>
<P>
Allen and his colleagues have held their board meeting in Beijing
during their visit here. Before coming to Beijing, they had visited
Shanghai and inspected the Sino-US petro-chemical projects in that
city.
</P>
<P>
Later today, the China Petro-chemical Corporation and Phillips
Petroleum Company signed a letter of intent on the establishment
of a large-scale ethylene project in Lanzhou, Northwest China's
Gansu Province, and a K-resin project in Shanghai, and the
expansion of a polyethylene project in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the hi-tech petro-chemical project in
Lanzhou is to produce polyethylene and polypropylene
materials. The project involves a total investment of over 2
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Zeng Peiyan, vice-minister of the State Planning Commission,
Sheng Huaren, President of the China Petro-chemical Corporation,
and Guo Kun, vice-governor of Gansu Province, were present at the
meeting.  
</P>
