<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhuhai to Host 2nd Major Air Show in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Second China International
Aviation and Aerospace Exposition will be held in the thriving
south China city of Zhuhai in November 1998.
</P>
<P>
The first air show was held in the city bordering Macao in
November 1996.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai Mayor Liang Guangda announced the establishment of the
organizing committee headed by Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo here in
Beijing today. The event will be jointly sponsored by the Civil
Aviation Administration of China, Aviation Industries of China,
China Aerospace Corp. and the Zhuhai government.
</P>
<P>
Liang said that several well-known aerospace companies,
including US-based Lockheed Martin and Alenia of Italy, have
announced their intention to participate in the exposition, with
industry leaders such as Boeing, Airbus Industrie, Rolls Royce,
BMW and Benz also expected to attend.
</P>
<P>
The event will feature commercial flight demonstrations, as
well precision military flight teams from China, Russia, the
United States and France, according to Liang.
</P>
<P>
He said the Zhuhai government allocated substantial funding to
expand the parking apron at the local airport, with the total
capacity currently ranging between 100-200 aircraft. The city has
also constructed a press center covering 8,000 sq.m. and a
commercial center with floor space of 10,000 sq.m.
</P>
<P>
A parking lot covering 80,000 sq.m., an eight-lane ring road
and several hotels are currently under construction around the
exposition site adjacent to the Zhuhai airport.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
