<HEADLINE> China to Raise Massive Funds for Transportation Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- China will raise a fund of 830
billion yuan through every possible channel for 340 key projects
of its transportation industry in the 1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
Li Duanshen, head of the transportation and energy department
of the State Planning Commission, said at a press conference here
today that China's cargo transportation volume will hit 16 billion
tons in the year 2000, and passenger transportation volume will
reach 17.5 billion people, with the annual growth amounting to 5.2
percent and 8.3 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the industry grew at a high speed during the
1991-1995 period. Cargo transportation volume rose by 2.5 percent
to reach 12.7 billion tons in 1996, while the passenger
transportation volume scored 12.5 billion people, up 6.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The state will continue to offer the sector preferential
policies and set up a special fund to increase its comprehensive
transportation capacity in the coming years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
