<HEADLINE> Mosley Re-elected FIA President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Briton Max Mosley was re-elected
president of the International Automobile Federation (FIA)
unanimously on Friday, a FIA spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Mosley was re-elected for a second four-year term at FIA's
Paris headquarters by delegates from 82 countries and regions, he
said.
</P>
<P>
The Briton was first voted as president in 1993. 
