<HEADLINE> Kuwait to Offer Syria Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait will offer Syria a 65
million-U.S.-dollar loan to help finance a major communications
project, official Syrian daily Al Thawrah reported today.
</P>
<P>
The loan falls within the framework of an agreement signed
here Thursday by Syrian Minister of State for Planning Affairs Abdel
Rahim al-Soubei and Badr Mashari Al Hameidi, Director General of
the Kuwaiti Arab Development Fund.
</P>
<P>
The loan will help finance a communications project which will
meet the rising demand for communication services in Syrian towns
and villages.
</P>
<P>
The loan will cover 8.45 percent of the overall cost of the
project. The overall cost amounts to 33.97 billion Syrian liras
(790 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Hameidi arrived here Wednesday on a visit to Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
