<HEADLINE> Tan Shuping Wins 3m Springboard Title at National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Tan Shuping, a native of
Guangxi, outscored her rivals to take the women's three-meter
springboard title at the Eighth National Games here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Despite injuries have been plagueing her for years, Tan, the
best springboard diver in China after Gao Min retired in 1992,
collected a total of 559.47 points for the top honour.
</P>
<P>
Tan who surprisingly failed in the qualifying rounds in
Atlanta, had a steady performance in her five dives in the finals,
including a difficult 107c combination.
</P>
<P>
Guo Jingjing from Hebei province, who ranked first in the
semifinals, finished second with a combined point of 553.86, while
Rao Lang of Sichuan province took home the bronze medal with
512.52 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
