<HEADLINE> Nigeria May Issue New 100 Naira </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government may
introduce a new 100 Naira note in next year's budget, the
Nigerian tribune reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a reliable source as saying that the issue
of bigger notes is contained in the final report of the vision
2010 committee, the country's first long-term planning body, to
the head of state, General Sani Abacha in late September.
</P>
<P>
The committee has recommended that the maximum denomination of
the currency be progressively reviewed to reflect the trend of
inflation, the source said.
</P>
<P>
There has been a pressure on the government to issue bigger
notes, in view of the massive depreciation of Naira in the past
years and the higher costs it poses to business activities.
</P>
<P>
The maximum note now is 50 naira. 
</P>
</TEXT>
