<HEADLINE> Ince to Be Captain in Saturday's World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Paul Ince of England will lead
England team in Saturday's crucial World Cup qualifier against
Italy.
</P>
<P>
The Liverpool midfielder captain has led England four times
previously. He was the country's first black captain in 1993
U.S. Cup when England defeat the Americans in Boston.
</P>
<P>
Ince, who has played in the Olympic Stadium of Rome twice when
he was with Inter Milan, knew well about the venue.
</P>
<P>
The decision made by coach Glenn Hoddle meant that there might
be a massive doubt over whether Arsenal defender Tony Adams would
be fit to play.
</P>
<P>
Adams, whom had been expected to be the team's captain, has
just went through an ankle operation and a rib injury. 
</P>
