<HEADLINE> Teenage Rider Hurt in Cycling Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Larisa Tchouenko of Belarus was
injured in a crash at the junior women's road race of the world
cycling championships in San Sebastian on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Tchouenko, while riding in the leading pack, crashed to the
ground as her front wheel hit the foot of a crowd barrier.
</P>
<P>
The Belarussian girl lay stunned with her face swollen, but
recovered consciousness as the paramedics fitted a neck brace.
</P>
<P>
Mirella van Melis won the Netherlands' first gold medal in the
championships, beating Switzerland's Nicole Braendli and Sofie
Andersson of Sweden, at the home stretch of the 67.5 kilometers
race. 
</P>
