<HEADLINE> One Fifth German Overweight, Expert Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- About one fifth of German adults
and 15 to 20 percent of German children are too fat mainly due to
irregular meals, too much fastfood as well as excessive time
watching TV, a German health expert said today.
</P>
<P>
According to Johannes Georg Wechsler, president of the German
Adipositas Association, overweight is a chronic disease that must
be treated seriously.
</P>
<P>
However, he also warned against quick diets and self medication
through intake of medicines like laxative or dehydration compound.
</P>
<P>
Instead, he recommended proper food and regular exercises.
"Intensive walking for one hour everyday is more successful than
jogging," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
