<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OAU: No Referendum on Comoros' Anjouan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) urged the Comoran separatists to abstain from
organizing a referendum for self determination on the island of
Anjouan before the international conference on the recent
situation of Comoros is convened.
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release issued here today, the
central organ passed the decision at its 38th ordinary session
held here Thursday in order to consider the report of the OAU
secretary general on the situation in Comoros.
</P>
<P>
The press release said, the central organ warned the
separatists that it would not recognize the outcome of any such
referendum and appealed to all the Comoran parties to refrain
from any acts likely to further complicate the situation and
undermine the process of dialogue as well as national
reconciliation.
</P>
<P>
It requested the secretary general to move immediately so that
the conference could be convened as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
OAU also listened to a statement on the Congolese crisis by
Ambassador Victor Nimi, permanent representative of the Republic
of Congo. It welcomed the signing by President Pascal Lissouba
and Bernard Kolelas, of the ceasefire agreement proposed by the
international mediation.
</P>
<P>
It also urged all the Congolese parties concerned to
immediately end fighting.
</P>
<P>
The central organ called upon the secretary general to
intensify consultations with the United Nations and the African
countries for the speedy deployment of the proposed peace-keeping
force in the Republic of Congo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
