<HEADLINE> One in Every 50 Vietnamese Subscribes to Phone Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- One in every 50 Vietnamese are
currently subscribing to the telephone service, said the Vietnam
Posts and Telecommunications Corporation (VNPT) today.
</P>
<P>
The recent 1.5 million telephone subscribers nationwide,
according to a report released by the state-owned VNPT, represent
a 100 percent increase over the country's total in late 1995.
</P>
<P>
The VNPT has digitalized over 90 percent of the country's
telecom network, including 2,900 communication channels available
via an undersea cable and 1,334 others through a satellite network.
</P>
<P>
The Integrated Digital Network (IDN) is expected to be replaced
next year by the Integrated Service Digital Network (ISDN).
</P>
<P>
However, the International Telecommunications Union (ITU) said
the current high growth rate has to continue into the year 2000 to
wire phone lines into the homes of 5-6 percent of the population.
</P>
<P>
On its part, the VNPT said Vietnam's post and telecommunications
industry needs an annual investment equivalent to 300-500 million
U.S. dollars through the end of this century to achieve the goal.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
