<HEADLINE> Dupont Expands Chinese Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Stacey Mobley, senior vice
president of the multi-national Dupont predicted Dupont's
investment in China would reach one billion US dollars by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
Mobley made the predictment in Beijing Thursday following his
trip to Shanghai where Dupont held its Asian-Pacific regional
business meeting. He said this is the first time for Dupont's
senior executives to attend a regional business meeting in Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Our choosing of China (as the meeting venue) demonstrates
Dupont has attached great importance to Chinese market," said
Mobley, adding that China would be a global economic center in the
21st century and also an important market for Dupont's global
business expansion.
</P>
<P>
"I think it's rewarding to see China with my own eyes," said
Mobley who is visiting China for the first time. "I am quite
impressed that China is full of vitality."
</P>
<P>
The vice president announced yesterday that Dupont will launch
a scholarship in Beijing University. So far the multinational has
set up scholarships in 16 Chinese colleges and universities that
total nearly one million yuan.
</P>
<P>
It has three solely-funded enterprises and eight joint ventures
in China with investment already exceeding 300 million US
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
