<HEADLINE> National Cotton Fair Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Cotton suppliers and buyers from
all over the country are gathering in Beijing for a national
cotton trade fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair which opened yesterday, the third of its kind, is
designed to provide a chance for a direct meeting of the suppliers
and the buyers.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous two fairs, this year's event
attracts much more participants -- 195 suppliers and 410 buyers.
</P>
<P>
The suppliers not only include cotton traders from
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, a leading cotton grower, but
also companies at least at the county-level from across the
country.
</P>
<P>
All textile enterprises, no matter what their ownership, are
also allowed to buy cotton at the fair, sources said.
</P>
<P>
A national cotton fair coordination group has made specific
requirements on the amount of the cotton traded, the price, and
the cotton purchasing principal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
