<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Review Tariffs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is to review trade
tariffs in a bid to enhance cross-border trade with Uganda, The
Monitor today quoted Tanzanian President Benjamin Mpaka as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the fifth International Trade Fair of Uganda
Manufacturers Association here Wednesday, the president
underlined the importance of free trade for the region.
</P>
<P>
Mpaka said he visits Uganda twice within two months to
encourage the cross-border trade with Uganda.
</P>
<P>
Investment to Africa from the developed countries is reducing
from 13.9 billions in 1990 of U.S. Dollars to 11.7 billions by
1994, and Africans cannot get modern technologies from the first
world to manufacture competitive products, the Tanzanian
president noted, adding that it is important to form regional
blocs to safeguard the interest of African countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
