<HEADLINE> Ten Mln US Dollars Agreement for Sino-British Engine Producers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Britain's Rolls-Royce Group, a
major engine producer in the world, will purchase more than ten
million US dollars worth of engine parts from China's Xi'an Aero
Engine Corporation (XAE) in the coming six years.
</P>
<P>
This is in accordance with a long-term cooperative agreement
signed here today by the Rolls-Royce and the Aviation Industries
of China and the China National Aero-Technology Import and Export
Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The agreement says that the XAE will produce steel and light
alloy ring components suitable for a wide range of Rolls-Royce
engines including the Trent 700, which powers the Airbus Industrie
A330, and the Trent 800, which powers the Boeing 777.
</P>
<P>
Rolls-Royce aero engines are today in operation or on order
with ten Chinese operators. Sources say that the British producer
and China's XAE have begun to jointly build a casting and
machinery processing center, and will put it into operation next
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
