<HEADLINE> Australian Breaks Commonwealth Swimming Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Matthew Dunn Friday broke the
Commonwealth record in the 200-meter individual medley in Brisbane
at the Australian trials for the world swimming championships.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old clocked a new Commonwealth record of two
minutes, 0.99 seconds which is the second-fastest time in the
world this year.
</P>
<P>
Only Dutch swimmer Marcel Wouda has gone faster than Dunn this
year, clocking 2:00.77 at the European championships in August.
</P>
<P>
Dunn's time took 0.14 seconds off Canadian Curtis Myden's time
of 2:01.13 set at the Atlanta Olympics last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
