<HEADLINE> China Southwestern Airlines to Purchase Three A340 Airliners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The China Southwestern Airlines
has ordered three A340-300 airliners from the European Airbus
Industrie.
</P>
<P>
The four-motor airplane has 370 seats. According to their
agreement, two airliners will be delivered in the second half of
1998, and another one, in 1999.
</P>
<P>
The airliners will be used on some of the Southwestern's
domestic air routes, including one from Chengdu to Lhasa, which is
blamed for its flight difficulty as Lhasa airport is surrounded by
mountains in three sides, and is 3,570 meters above the sea level,
one of the highest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The China Southwestern Airlines, based Chengdu, capital of
southwest China's Sichuan Province, is the third Chinese customer
of the Airbus, following the China Eastern Airlines and Air China.
</P>
<P>
So far, the A330/340 family has got confirmed orders for 389
airliners, sources say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
