<HEADLINE> Maize Price Up in E. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Maize price has gone up from
180 Uganda Shillings a kilogram in earlier September to between
260 and 275 shillings now in Jinja, eastern Uganda, The New
Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
The eastern part is the main grain producer in the country.
</P>
<P>
Haruna Muguwa, a maize dealer and maize flour producer in
Jinja said the farmers in the region now are hoarding their grain
for a better price.
</P>
<P>
The government officials warned earlier that a famine is
loomed due to the prolonged drought this year. In some parts of
the east, local authorities established check points to prevent
transporting grains from the region.
</P>
<P>
The price of maize flour has risen from 350 shillings in
September to 600 now in the city, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
