<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ten Chinese Athletes Fail Doping Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Ten Chinese athletes were
tested positive for doping this year as the country is to stage
its largest Eighth National Games of the century, a sports
official revealed here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The anti-doping commission of the Olympic Committee of China
has conducted a total of 2,500 tests this year, and all the
athletes who have registered for the Games are eligible for the
random tests, said Wu Shouzhang, director of the competition
department of the Games.
</P>
<P>
The ten positive cases included those in the qualifying rounds
for the Games whereas none of the case was caught in the finals of
those sports conducted prior to the official opening of the Games,
Wu said.
</P>
<P>
The official failed to reveal the names of the athletes and
their respective sports.
</P>
<P>
However, Wu said that the commission will spare no efforts in
its anti-doping battle during the Games which runs from October
12-24. 
</P>
</TEXT>
