<HEADLINE> Swedish Shares Tumble As Germany Raises Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, October 10 (Xinhua)-- Swedish stocks fell by 2
percent and bonds prices tumbled on Thursday, after the German
Bundesbank raised interest rates, according to press here today.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Bundesbank raised its most important rate, the
repurchase or repo rate to 3.30 percent from an all-time-low of
3.0 percent, in a preemptive strike against mounting inflation
pressures and to smooth the path to a common European currency in
1999.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson, Sweden's largest company by market capitalization,
fell 3.5 kronor to SEK 368. Swedish drug-maker Astra, fell 2.5
kronor to 127.5. 
</P>
