<HEADLINE> Eight Killed, 65 Injured in India's Accidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Eight people were killed and
65 others injured in various accidents in India in the past 24
hours.
</P>
<P>
Two persons were killed and 10 others injured, some of them
seriously, when a truck fell down a bridge in West Delhi early
today, the Press Trust of India said here.
</P>
<P>
The truck driver lost control while taking a sharp turn to
avoid a head-on collision with a tempo.
</P>
<P>
Four members of a family were crushed to death under the
Mumbai-Howrah mail train last night when they were trying to cross
the tracks.
</P>
<P>
According to another report, two persons were killed and 55
others injured when a canon exploded during religious festival
celebrations at the Sarbamangala Temple near Calcutta late last
night.
</P>
<P>
The canon, fired every year as part of the celebrations, burst
as it was being loaded with gunpowder. Fire broke out immediately
after the explosion, injuring many onlookers who were there to
witness the ceremony.  
</P>
