<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Launch Police Database System This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The Association of
Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) will officially launch a system in
Singapore by the end of this year for cooperation among its member
police forces to fight international crimes, the Singapore police
chief said today.
</P>
<P>
The system, known as "Aseanapol Database System," is being
developed by a team comprising representatives of ASEAN member
police forces and staff of an international consultancy firm, Khoo
Boon Hui, who is on a visit here, told reporters after talks with
Malaysia's Inspector-General of Police Abdul Rahim Noor.
</P>
<P>
He said the system would contain information on cross-border
criminal activities, which would enable the ASEAN police forces to
exchange criminal records and information on a regional basis,
thus marking an important step forward in fighting international
crimes.
</P>
<P>
The database will be vital in combating crimes such as drug
trafficking, forgery of travel documents and currency
counterfeiting, he said.
</P>
<P>
"It has taken some time to get all the member nations to come
together to finance and develop the system and we will wait for
the other countries to get on board before we officially launch
the system," Khoo said. "I believe we should be able to get
everything together by the end of the year."
</P>
<P>
ASEAN at present groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar,
Laos, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Khoo also said cooperation between Singapore and Malaysian
police has always been excellent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Malaysian police chief said relations between
the two police forces of the two neighbors have always been good
and a model for other countries.
</P>
<P>
Abdul Rahim told reporters that during their hour-long talks,
they covered expanding cooperation in crime prevention, police
training and education in both countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
