<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets With Mercosur Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met with a delegation from South
American Common Market (Mercosur) here today.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is led by Agustin Espinosa, director-general for
Integration and Mercosur Affairs of the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs of Uruguay that is in exercise of the Presidency pro
tempore of Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the
Chinese government, Qian welcomed the Mercosur delegation to China
for the first China-Mercosur Dialogue in Beijing on behalf of the
Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
He said the Chinese Government is delighted to see the growth
of friendly cooperation between China and Latin American countries
in all fields such as politics and economy.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, an important organization of economic integration in
Latin America, has broad prospects for development, he noted,
adding that the two sides enjoy a great potential of economic and
trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of an effective framework for dialogue and
cooperation between the two sides will be good for promoting the
expansion of bilateral relations, especially the continued growth
of economic and trade cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian thanked Espinosa for Mercosur's support for China's
accession to the World Trade Organization (WTO). He also briefed
the guests on China's internal situation and foreign policies.
</P>
<P>
Espinosa said that Mercosur attaches importance to its
relations with China and is ready to promote economic and trade
cooperation with China through all channels. He added that because
of its important role in today's world, China should become an
indispensable cooperative partner of Mercosur's.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur consists of four member nations, namely Brazil,
Argentina, Uruguay and Paraguay.  
</P>
