<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Host ASEAN Conference on Finance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will host an
ASEAN Conference and Exhibition on Finance from December 1 to 3 in
conjunction with the 30th anniversary of the regional grouping, it
was officially reported today.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN finance ministers and senior officials will attend the
conference and exhibition, with the theme "ASEAN Financial
Initiatives for the 21st Century," the Malaysian national news
agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
Senior representatives from international organizations such as
the International Monetary Fund (IMF) and the World Bank will also
take part in the event to be organized by the ASEAN Business Forum
(ABF) in cooperation with the ASEAN Secretariat, it said.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad will open the
conference and exhibition and deliver a keynote address and IMF
Managing Director Michel Camdessus is expected to give a talk at a
special session on "The Road Ahead for Global Financial Markets --
Smooth or Rocky."
</P>
<P>
President of the European Monetary Institute Alexandre
Lamfalussy is also expected to give a talk entitled "EURO 1999:
Implications for Global Economic Growth and Financial Market
Stability," the report said.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted ASEAN Secretary-General Ajit Singh as
saying that considering the recent crisis in the region's currency
market, the conference will be particularly relevant to policy
makers who have to deal with the challenges of globalization in
the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, Myanmar, Laos,
Singapore. the Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
