girl, has become the youngest in this eastern China metropolis to
obtain a certificate in operation of office automatic apparatus.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, a third-year student from No. 3 Primary School of Xikang
Road, recently passed a municipal examination on the ability to
use computer.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to her father, a computer teacher, Jiang started to
learn using computer in an early age and has achieved thus the
proficiency in computer application.
</P>
<P>
Computer operators are among the most sought after personnel in
Shanghai, which is witnessing a thriving economy. Some 1.1 million
local residents have taken examinations on computer application,
in which more than 600,000 have passed the tests.
</P>
<P>
A recent sample survey shows that eight percent of Shanghai
families have bought a computer.  
