by 1.24 dollars to finish at 5.3 Singapore dollars. The Singapore
Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign increased by 1 dollar to end at 22.7
Singapore dollars while Uniphoenix went up by 80 cents to close at
7.45 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, NST was the biggest loser as it declined by
4.8 dollars to end at 4.7 Singapore dollars. BMT 100 fell by 2
dollars to close at 86 dollars. MISC Foreign lost 26 cents to
finish at three dollars.  
