<HEADLINE> Israel Imposes Closure on Palestinian Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Israeli army imposed today a
general closure on the West Bank and Gaza Strip for the coming
Jewish holiday Yom Kippur (Day of Atonement), which will begin
tonight and last two days.
</P>
<P>
The closure will remain in effect until midnight Saturday,
and during the period Palestinians will be barred from entering
Israel. But the army said that for emergency humanitarian
reasons some Palestinians will be allowed in.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces called on all the Palestinians working
in Israel to leave the country and return home by 2 p.m. today.
</P>
<P>
Israel has periodically sealed off the West Bank and Gaza for
security reasons since parts of the territories fell under
Palestinian self-rule in 1994 under its peace deals with the
Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, there have been clashes between Israeli soldiers
and Palestinians in recent days since Israel began demolishing
some Palestinian buildings in the Israel-occupied areas.
</P>
<P>
Two Palestinian merchants were arrested Tuesday when 20
merchants attempted to prevent their stalls from being
dismantled near Halhoul, southeast to Jerusalem. Witnesses
said that Israeli soldiers arrived in the area with a
bulldozer and demolished these stalls.
</P>
<P>
Also in the Hebron area in West Bank, eight Palestinian stalls
were dismantled, as Israel said that the stalls posed a traffic
hazard and caused numerous accidents when cars stopped to
purchase goods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
