<DOCNO> XIE19971010.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 08:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FAO Highlights Participatory Approach to Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The best approach to eradicate
poverty and hunger is to help the poor help themselves, Jacques
Diouf, Director-General of the Food and Agriculture Organization
(FAO) of the United Nations has said.
</P>
<P>
"Our organization is helping those poor countries to produce
food instead of asking for food. It's better to teach people the
technique of fishing than give them fish," the FAO chief told
reporters upon his arrival at the Cairo airport Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
He was speaking about FAO's Special Program For Food Security
which is designed to help low-income food-deficit countries,
faced with food shortfalls, limited funds to finance imports and
declining food aid, to increase food production and productivity
quickly and sustainably.
</P>
<P>
Diouf, coming here a week before the World Food Day, said
he will review with Egyptian leaders the developments on
agriculture and food production after the 1996 World Food Summit
when 186 countries pledged to halve the number of undernourished
people in the world by 2015.
</P>
<P>
Painting a bleak picture for food situation in Africa,
however, Diouf said 40 of the world's 86 lowest-food income
countries are in this continent which is habitated by merely 11
percent of the world people.
</P>
<P>
Diouf described Africa as the place with the most serious
problems of food because it is the only continent where
agricultural production per capita has gone down in the last 20
years and which has one of the highest rate of population versus
crops.
</P>
<P>
"Even the improvement in crop production (in Africa) this year
can be largely contributed to the good rain and good climate," he
lamented.
</P>
<P>
He urged African countries, where only 8 percent of arable land
has water control, to build their own system of water control to
secure stability in food provision and less dependency on climate.
</P>
<P>
The FAO has directed many activities in many parts of the
world with a view to helping them achieve productivity necessary
to overcome increase in population, according to the
U.N. official.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the FAO is advising governments on how to improve
their agricultural policies to create an environment more
favorable to investment in favor of farmers and address
constraint on infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, farmers choose and demonstrate selected
improved technologies to fellow farmers during a pilot phase. The
focus is on improved water control, intensification of crop
production through, for example, introduction of improved
varieties, diversification of production systems and analysis of
constraints faced by farmers.
</P>
<P>
Successful strategies are then made available during an
expansion phase.
</P>
<P>
According to the FAO chief, by mid-1997 the food security
program was already operational in 19 countries including 10 in
Africa and being formulated in other 32 countries.
</P>
<P>
He cited a Special Program project under way in China's
Sichuan province as an excellent example of cooperation and one
of the best FAO programs implemented.
</P>
<P>
Yields of wheat, rice and maize in demonstration sites in
1995/96 were estimated to be higher by 19 to 27 percent than in
the preceding year in Sichuan province, before the introduction
of the Special Program, according to a FAO report.
</P>
<P>
According to FAO, 27 million people worldwide face food
emergencies because of man-made or natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The world's agricultural production has risen by 35 percent
since 1980, and by 68 percent in the developing world, but
because of population increases, the per capita figures are not so
positive, up by only 5 percent overall and 25 percent in
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Projections suggest that by the year 2015, the world's
population will be around 8.3 billion. To feed this number of
people, world food production will have to be more than double
the present level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971010.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
