<HEADLINE> Beijing Gets 900 New Mobile Phone Users Every Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Nine hundred people are added
to the rolls of mobile phone services every day in the Chinese
capital.
</P>
<P>
The number of mobile phone customers is now 570,000, meaning
five mobile phones for every 100 people.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's mobile phone service began in 1987. The number of
mobile phone users more than doubled each year after that.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Telecom has built more than 360 base stations for its
GSM digital mobile phone network that covers the the entire city,
including the subway.
</P>
<P>
The GSM network also provides a roaming service for 30
provinces, cities, and autonomous regions, and 13 countries and
regions from Singapore to Finland.  
