announced by Iraqi diplomat Al-Yacoubi in Rome at a press
conference on the eve of the United Nations' decision not to ease
the embargo, which is reviewed every six months.
(Italy-Iraq-Trade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
XI'AN, China -- Taking the advantage of the decision of the
Chinese government to place greater importance on developing
western parts of the country, Xi'an, a famous ancient city, has
opened its door wider to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Feng Xuchu said that 1,743 overseas-funded enterprises
have been set up in Xi'an, a city with a history of more than
3,100 years. Now the ancient city is the capital of Shaanxi
province in the Northwest. (China-Xi'an-Overseas Investment)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SHENYANG, China -- Since China started its reforms and opening
up in the late '70s, the Chinese have become more careful about
their appearance and the people of northeast China's Liaoning
province are no exception.
</P>
<P>
There are now more than 5,000 beauty parlors in the province, a
four-fold increase from five years ago.
(China-Liaoning-Beauty-Parlors)
