<HEADLINE> Tourism Growing Near China's Three Gorges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The city of Yichang near the
Three Gorges on the Yangtze River has increased tourism by making
use of the Three Gorges Dam project, according to Vice-mayor Zhang
Jianyi.
</P>
<P>
The city is rich in scenic places, with its gorges and dams,
some remnants of the Three Kingdoms Period (220-265) in the east,
in the west, the Three Gorges, and in the north, the well-known
exploration spot of Shennongjia.
</P>
<P>
More than 15,000 people are involved in the tourism business,
which has fixed assets of one billion yuan (about 125 million US
dollars), said Zhang. The city has spent some 800 million yuan on
scenic resources and infrastructure for tourism.
</P>
<P>
The city has improved controls on the tourism business in the
past several years, and has penalized a number of tourist agencies
that have overcharged customers.
</P>
<P>
With improvements in the business, the number of visitors has
grown. Tourist arrivals have totalled 30 million in the past few
years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
