<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparations Complete for 15th World Petroleum Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Preparations have been
completed for the 15th World Petroleum Congress (WPC) scheduled
for October 12-16 in Beijing, which is expected to draw 4,300
representatives from 88 countries.
</P>
<P>
Wang Tao, chairman of the Chinese Organizing Committee of the
15th WPC, told a news conference today that attendance should be
the largest in the congress' history.
</P>
<P>
Presidents from 68 international and state petroleum companies
are expected to attend, as well as ministers of petroleum or
energy from 20 countries, senior officers of the WPC and
representatives from the World Energy Council and International
Gas Union.
</P>
<P>
Extensive discussions will focus on the theme of "Technology
and Globalization -- Leading the Petroleum Industry into the 21st
Century."
</P>
<P>
Wang said the five-day congress will consist of six plenary
addresses, 21 panel forums, 10 review and forecast reports and a
ministerial forum. In addition, 93 papers will be presented to the
congress and 238 papers will be offered for academic exchange.
</P>
<P>
He said that all reports and papers will focus on issues of oil
exploration, development and drilling, processing technology,
natural gas, oil and gas reserves, environmental protection and
transportation.
</P>
<P>
Oil experts will conduct exchanges on the latest scientific and
technological results concerning oil production as well as the
opportunities and challenges facing the world petroleum industry
in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
During the congress, the WPC organizing committee will hold an
international exhibition on oil, gas and
petrochemicals. Six-hundred companies and enterprises will display
their latest scientific and technological findings, equipment and
products.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the upcoming congress, China set up its WPC
organizing committee in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The WPC was established in London in 1933, with its first
congress held the same year. It now has 47 members, including the
world's major oil producers and consumers.
</P>
<P>
The WPC is held every three years. China, a member since 1979,
will host the conference for the first time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
