<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe Ratifies Five Loan Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, October 10 (xinhua) -- Zimbabwean parliament yesterday
ratified five loan agreements between the government of Zimbabwe
and five international institutions worth 625.65 million Zimbabwe
Dollars (50 million U.S. Dollars).
</P>
<P>
Minister of Finance Herbert Murerwa presented the loan
agreements and their terms amid very little resistance from the
legislators who earlier this year fought hard against loans to
finance the construction of the new Harare international airport
terminal.
</P>
<P>
The minister said none of the funds secured under the loan
agreements had been utilized as the government awaited the
approval of the house.
</P>
<P>
"I would like to assure you that the government continues to
be cautious of its debt service capitalization and hence we have
tried to source for very soft loans," said Murerwa, adding that
the money were part of the 1997/98 budget.
</P>
<P>
The five loans will be provided by the Nordic Development
Fund, the International Development Association, the Spanish
Development Aid Fund, the Banco Exterior de Espana and Societe
Generale of France. 
