<HEADLINE> Beijing Holding International Power Equipment Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- An international power equipment
and technology exhibition is being held at the China International
Exhibition Center in Beijing, attracting businesses from 17
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
On display are Equipment and technology used in thermal and
hydroelectric power, high-power transmission, transformer
substations, and electricity for urban areas.
</P>
<P>
Some big names have joined the event to discuss investment
opportunities in China, including ABB and Japan's Mitsubishi Heavy
Industries Ltd. and Mitsubishi Electric.
</P>
<P>
Company representatives will hold seminars on developing the
power industry.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is sponsored by the Beijing Municipal Branch of
the China Council for the Promotion of International Trade and the
Beijing Institute of Electrical Engineering.  
</P>
