<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Divers Show Apathy for Springboards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Shedding the aura as a "Diving
Kingdom", China is unbelievably facing a break-down of echelons as
its women divers were developing a trend of apathy for the
springboard events.
</P>
<P>
Experts warned that China would sacrifice its dominance on the
springboards unless authorities concerned unleashed unremitting
efforts to encourage its women divers to take on the traditional
sport with great enthusiasm.
</P>
<P>
"To evaluate the Eighth National Games, we are not ready for
any celebration as the Games failed to produce any promising women
springboard divers, not even a batch of new faces of potentials,"
said international judge Xuan Zengyong.
</P>
<P>
The springboards for women have been the strong fortress for
China as both Gao Min and Tan Shuping combined to make a clean
sweep of all major international titles.
</P>
<P>
Gao Min was bestowed as "diving queen" prior to her retirement
after the Barcelona Olympic Games in 1992 and Tan Shuping stepped
into her footsteps to take reign of the event in the succeeding
two years.
</P>
<P>
Yet, misfortunes plagued Tan Shuping time and again since 1994
and her injuries from shoulder to knees deprived her of daily
routine trainings, which fairly explained her drop-out from the
finals in the Atlanta Centennial Olympic Games in 1996.
</P>
<P>
After the retirment of Queen Gao, the Chinese diving officials
then pinned hopes upon another genious diver Fu Mingxia to switch
from platform to springboard who survived the pressure to win the
title in Atlanta in her debut in the 3-meter springboard.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Fu Mingxia submitted her retirement application right
after the Centennial Olympiad due to fatigue and injuries, forcing
the Chinese officials and coaches to cry for any hopefuls of great
potentials.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, coach Wu Guocun exploited his know-how
to help training injury-plagued Tan Shuping for a promising
recovery. Yet, Tan Shuping, a native of Guangxi, still faced a
menace of deteriorating her injuries which may eventully killed
her diving career, coach Wu lamented.
</P>
<P>
Even then, Tan Shuping, who was clearly not in her top form,
still enjoyed her up-onemanship in the National Games wherein no
chief rivals have the calibre to beat her with confidence.
</P>
<P>
The miserable but true fact can be well explained by the
experts who pinpointed out that "many a women divers are flocking
to platform wherein good scores and great feats are relatively
easier to be achieved compared to springboards."
</P>
<P>
The intriguing tricks justified the abnormal phenomenon of a
striking contrast between a flood of platform divers against the
drought of springboard trainees.
</P>
<P>
Judge Xuan Zengyong said that China still boasted of a pool of
almost 10 divers of great potentials for platform in the coming
Asian Games and the Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
But "where are our hopefuls for the springboards in the 2000
Sydney Games," the judge asked with concerns that locked between
his eyebrows. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
