<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dhaka Continues Promoting U.N. Principles: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will continue to make
its sincere and earnest endeavor for the promotion of the
principles and purposes of the U.N. Charter and to strengthen and
reinforce the U.N. role, Foreign Secretary Mustfizur Rahman said.
</P>
<P>
"Our commitment to the U.N. and the principles and purposes of
its charter have been affirmed and reaffirmed a number of times,
beginning with our declaration of independence," Rahman was quoted
today by the national news agency Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha as
saying Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Our constitution specifically stipulates that our
international relations shall be based on the principles
enunciated in the U.N. Charter," he said in a lecture on
"Bangladesh and the United Nations" here.
</P>
<P>
He said it has always been Bangladesh's contention that it is
the smaller and more vulnerable group of countries that have the
most vital stakes in an effective and dynamic United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The main purposes of the United Nations include the maintenance
of international peace and security, the development of friendly
relations among nations, the promotion of higher living standards
and conditions for economic and social progress and development,
he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The foreign secretary stressed that the United Nations has been
playing a harmonizing role in the attainment of these goals.
</P>
</TEXT>
