<HEADLINE> IOC Chief to Attend Chinese National Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Juan Antonio Samaranch,
president of the International Olympic Committee (IOC), will pay a
special visit here to attend the opening ceremony of China's
Eighth National Games, which will ring up its curtain on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch will arrive in the metropolitan on Sunday and is
expected to deliver a speech at the opening ceremony in the night.
</P>
<P>
This will be the third time for the IOC chief to visit the port
city, the most populous and biggest in the country. He attended
the opening ceremonies of the Fifth National Games in 1983 and the
First East Asian Games in 1993.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Shanghai, Samaranch will cut the ribbon for
China's Fourth Sports Painting Exhibition next Monday.
</P>
<P>
The IOC chief will also sign his signatures for the local
sports enthusiasts along with Wu Shaozu, minister of the Chinese
State Physical Culture and Sports Commission and Gong Xueping,
vice mayor and vice chairman of the Games' Organizing Committee.
</P>
