<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Industrial Center to Promote Trade with Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai will increase economic
and trade co-operation with African countries over the next three
years.
</P>
<P>
As most African countries are recovering from negative economic
growth since the beginning of the 1990s, the municipal government
and enterprises will explore new trade, investment, commercial and
engineering possibilities.
</P>
<P>
The city will also provide more high quality and less expensive
products and technology for low-income customers in African
countries.
</P>
<P>
It has opened 23 firms in ten African countries with a total
investment of 17.5 million US dollars, and the majority are
showing a profit.
</P>
<P>
In the past three years, trade between Shanghai and Africa
increased at an average of 20 percent annually. From January 1994
to August this year, the city won the contracts worth 47 million
US dollars provide labor services and undertake construction
projects in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
