<HEADLINE> Gingrich: U.S. Congress to Welcome Chinese President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Congress welcomes
Chinese President Jiang Zemin's visit here later this month,
Speaker of the House of Representatives Newt Gingrich said today.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich made the remarks to Liu Huaqiu, director of the
Office of Foreign Affairs under China's State Council, who arrived
here Wednesday to further prepare the grounds for Jiang's visit.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting on Capitol Hill, Gingrich told Liu that
U.S. congressional leaders will jointly host a breakfast in
Jiang's honor, hoping his visit will achieve positive results.
</P>
<P>
Jiang's visit will be the first by a Chinese head of state to
the United States in 12 years. Late Chinese President Li Xiannian
visited Washington in 1985.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Gingrich, Liu expressed the belief that
U.S. Congress will continue to work for the success of President
Jiang's upcoming visit.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese official also held talks today with
U.S. President's National Security Advisor Samuel Berger, who
invited him to come here for a preparatory tour.
</P>
<P>
Berger said the United States attaches great importance to
Jiang's visit and President Bill Clinton is looking forward to
meeting his Chinese counterpart in this U.S. capital.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the visit will be successful and further improve
Sino-U.S. ties.
</P>
<P>
Liu believed that Jiang's visit is of tremendous significance
and will surely produce "positive and profound" impact on the
bilateral relationship between the two countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
