<DOCNO> XIE19971010.0200 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan's Exports Decline in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's exports declined
nearly two percent in September, 1997 over the corresponding
period of last year, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The overall performance of the trade sector during the first
quarter of the current fiscal year, starting July 1, 1997, also
remained sluggish, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, exports during the month of
September, 1997, totaled 666 million U.S. dollars as against 682
million dollars during the corresponding month of 1996, showing a
decline of 1.9 percent and a negative growth of 3.4 percent as
compared to 689 million dollars during August, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan's imports during September, 1997 totaled 952 million
dollars as compared to 938 million dollars during the
corresponding month of last year, said the sources. The trade
deficit during September, 1997 reached 286 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total exports during the first quarter of the current fiscal
year totaled 2.017 billion dollars, showing a total growth of only
5.3 percent as against the target of 15 percent, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Total imports during the first three months of the 1997-98
fiscal year stood at 2.653 billion dollars, indicating a trade
deficit of 636 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that a high-level meeting chaired by Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif was held on Thursday to look into the slow
performance of the trade sector.
</P>
<P>
The concerned authorities were directed to take adequate
measures for the improvement of exports, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani government has set its export target for the
1997-98 fiscal year at 9.57 billion dollars while import target at
11.9 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit of the country in 1996-97 fiscal year stood
at 3.3 billion dollars. The government plans to reduce it to 2.33
billion dollars in the current fiscal year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
