<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
finished higher today after drifting in the morning session in
response to a weaker close on Wall Street overnight.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 5 points higher at 2602 with a turnover
of 70 million NZ dollars (45 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The market saw another big rise in Fletcher Energy shares, up
28 cents to 731 cents. Also higher were Brierley Investment,
gaining 1c to 138c, Carter Holt Harvey, lifting 4c to 359c, and
Lion Nathan, climbing 9c to 399c.
</P>
<P>
However, a stronger NZSE40 was checked by Telecom, which eased
3c to 813. Also ending lower was Air New Zealand, dipping 3c to
279c.  
