<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South China's City Holds Traditional Mountain-Climbing Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, October 10 (Xinhua) -- The people of Guangzhou, the
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, recently celebrated
the Double Ninth Festival (9th day of the 9th lunar month) by
climbing up scenic Mount Baiyun (White Cloud).
</P>
<P>
It is a tradition of the Chinese people to climb up mountains
on the Double Ninth Festival, which falls on today this
year. Since 1982 the Guangzhou city has organized annual
mountain-climbing activities on the occasion. The activities have
attracted a great number of people.
</P>
<P>
Several thousand people from more than 100 local organizations
took part in this year's mountain-climbing celebration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
