<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Develop Rural Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh will try to develop
the rural areas which "are the lifeline of the country," the
independent United News of Bangladesh (UNB) today quoted Prime
Minister Sheikh Hasina as saying.
</P>
<P>
During a tour of a U.N.-sponsored project, the South Asia
Poverty Alleviation Program (SAPAP), Thursday, the prime minister
said, "The only target of the present government is to improve the
living condition of the people by ensuring massive economic
development, particularly in the rural areas."
</P>
<P>
"Economic activities in the rural areas will be accelerated if
government officials and employees fulfill their duties properly,"
said the prime minister, who asked the officials to work with
their utmost sincerity and dedication.
</P>
<P>
The aim of the government is to alleviate poverty in the
shortest possible time and ensure a better life for all, the prime
minister added.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh is an agriculture-based country with more than 80
percent of its 120 million people living in the rural areas, where
more than 50 percent of farmers are living under the poverty line.
</P>
<P>
Under the SAPAP project sponsored by the U.N. Development
Program with the help of some South Asian governments, various
steps are being taken to improve infrastructure facilities in the
country, the UNB said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
