<HEADLINE> East African Passports Available Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Immigration departments
of the East African Cooperation (EAC) member states will start
next month issuing common passports to citizens of Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Preparation for the new passports has completed, the press
quoted a spokesman of the Department of Immigration Service in
Dar es Salaam, Herbert Chilambo as confirming.
</P>
<P>
The new passports are intended to facilitate movement of
citizens of the three countries within the EAC region of Kenya,
Tanzania and Uganda who have a combined population of nearly 80
million.
</P>
<P>
Chilambo said, "The passports will be issued simultaneously in
the three east African states through the normal procedures."
</P>
<P>
He said that Tanzanians wishing to travel to any EAC partner
state can apply for the new passport. 
</P>
