<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Government Acknowledges Industrial Slowdown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- A discussion paper prepared
by the union Industry Ministry marks the center's first
acknowledgment of a slowdown in industrial activity, local
economic paper Business Standard said here today.
</P>
<P>
The paper will be taken up for discussion at the prime
minister's meeting with industry, scheduled for October 14. The
government's deep concern is apparent in the discussion paper.
</P>
<P>
The paper points out that there is wide perception that demand
is slackening for basic goods like steel and cement, paper and
newsprint, and commercial vehicles. A cutback in production and
underutilisation of capacities have been reported in several
sectors.
</P>
<P>
The paper attributes the industrial slowdown to
underperformance of certain key sectors like power, fertilizers,
consumer durables, crude petroleum and certain segments of the
capital goods sector.
</P>
<P>
This deceleration is also perceived to be a cumulative effect
of many macroeconomic factors including lower capital expenditure
by the government, subdued export growth and a slowdown in
investment and consumer demand in the non-governmental sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
