<HEADLINE> Official Sri Lankan Delegation Visits Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, October 10 (Xinhua) -- A Sri Lankan delegation led by
Deputy Foreign Minister Lakshman Kirielle will leave here this
evening for the Middle East to work out mechanisms to resolve the
problems of Sri Lankan expatriates, foreign ministry sources said
today.
</P>
<P>
During its ten-day mission there, the delegation will visit
Kuwait, Jordan, Abu Dhabi and Dubai where over 300,000 Sri Lankan
