<HEADLINE> Indonesia President Meets Malaysian King </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia could boost its
development through cooperation with other nations, President
Soeharto told visiting Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a state banquet held here in honor of the Malaysian
King, the president said, "We are aware that all development
burdens and responsibilities lie on the shoulders of the nation
concerned. But experience has shown that cooperation among nations
can be very beneficial."
</P>
<P>
The president admitted that the forest fires and the monetary
turmoil that hit Indonesia and other Southeast Asian nations
lately have hampered the pace of Indonesia's development efforts.
</P>
<P>
"We have done our utmost to overcome repeated disturbances to
our national development effort," the president said.
</P>
<P>
Raging fires have destroyed about 300,000 hectares of forest
land and caused heavy losses to the country's economy in the past
three months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the monetary crisis, which started in early July and
then spread to most parts of Southeast Asia, has forced a
depreciation of the Indonesian rupiah by 55 percent against the
U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian king and his wife Tuanku Najihah arrived here
Thursday for a six-day official visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto and the Malaysian king will hold talks this morning.
</P>
<P>
The king will also visit other places in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
