<HEADLINE> Italy's Industrial Orders Increase in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Italy's industrial orders rose 12.1
percent in July over the same period in 1996, the National
Statistics Institute (Istat) said today.
</P>
<P>
Orders increased in almost all sectors. Machine tools and
mechanical devices recorded a growth of 19.1 percent, metals 16
percent and means of transport 14.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Orders from abroad rose 7 percent over the first seven months
this year while domestic orders climbed 3.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
In July, sales of intermediate goods grew 7.4 percent, sales or
capital goods rose 7.2 percent, and consumer goods increased 4.9
percent, Istat reported. 
</P>
</TEXT>
