<HEADLINE> Peru Rejects Ecuador's Access Claim to Amazon River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Peru refused to negotiate with
Ecuador over its claim of sovereign access to the Amazon River,
Peruvian Foreign Minister Ferrero Costa said today.
</P>
<P>
Ferrero said at a press conference that this claim is
unacceptable because it refers to territories that were, are and
will be Peru's, historically and legally. "Peru does not negotiate
the cession of territories that are its own," he said.
</P>
<P>
Peru and Ecuador held five rounds of talks on border problems
from April to September in Brasilia, during which the two
countries stated their positions.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador raised its claim of sovereign access to the
Maranon-Amazones during the last round of discussions.
</P>
<P>
Ferrero said that the Peruvian delegation rejected Ecuador's
claim because it is a challenge to Peruvian sovereignty. 
</P>
