<HEADLINE> Large Enterprises Growing in East Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Sales of 12 major industrial
enterprises in Hefei, capital city of east China's Anhui province,
were 4.2 billion yuan in the first half of the year, accounting
for more than half of the total sales volume of the city's
important industrial businesses.
</P>
<P>
The Meiling Group, Rongshida Group, and Hefei Iron and Steel
Corp. had sales exceeding 600 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
A city government official in charge of industry attributes
these enterprises' "pillar role" to the government's efforts to
promote growth in large ventures at a low cost.
</P>
<P>
The city government is also placing great importance on helping
these enterprises use a modern managerial system to strengthen
their position in the market.
</P>
<P>
The managerial system focuses on capital expansion. As a
result, one company, the Anhui Motorcycle Company became one of
the city's top ten enterprises with the largest pre-tax profits,
after merging with a watch manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
The Rongshida Group increased its total capital to nearly two
billion yuan by getting 200 million yuan from overseas. Both
production and market share of its major product, a washing
machine, have maintained a leading position in China. 
</P>
