<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Decreases Sharply in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Albania's foreign trade volume
stood at 293.3 million U.S. dollars during the first half of this
year, equal to only 25 percent of last year's figure of 1.15
billion dollars for the same period.
</P>
<P>
The latest statistics from the Albanian national bank show that
the import volume decreased to 221.5 million dollars from 920.5
million dollars, while export volume dropped to 71.8 million
dollars from 228.8 million dollars in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The main cause was a national pyramid scheme, that wiped out
two billion U.S. dollars worth of Albanian's money and caused a
nationwide disturbance in the country.
</P>
<P>
Albania has experienced a large foreign deficit since 1994. The
export volume of the country in 1996 accounted for only 24.86
percent of the import volume. 
</P>
</TEXT>
