<HEADLINE> Reforms in Township Firms Accelerating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the leading port city
in north China, will help its township enterprises by merging them
into bigger company groups.
</P>
<P>
The local government has encouraged small businesses to come
together to improve competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
To date, a total of 131 company groups have been established by
enterprises with ten million yuan or more in assets each. These
groups have nearly ten billion yuan in fixed assets and employ
over 170,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises are playing an increasing role in
Tianjin's economy and now account for a third of the city's
industrial output and a fourth of its total exports. 
