<HEADLINE> Brazil Drafts Plan To Fight Illiteracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZILIA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government has
drawn a plan to teach reading and writing to nine million people
until the year 2004, an official said today.
</P>
<P>
The government is concerned by illiteracy in the country,
especially among women and has decided to mobilize all forces of
society to solve the problem, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Official data show that there are a total of 40 million
semi-illiterate people, half of them women older than 30, in this
South American country.
</P>
<P>
