<HEADLINE> China's Ancient City Opening up More to Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Taking the advantage of the
decision of the Chinese government to place greater importance on
developing western parts of the country, Xi'an, a famous ancient
city, has opened its door wider to overseas investors.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Feng Xuchu told Xinhua recently that 1,743
overseas-funded enterprises have been set up in Xi'an, a city with
a history of more than 3,100 years. Now the ancient city is the
capital of Shaanxi province in the Northwest.
</P>
<P>
By July this year, Xi'an had drawn a total of 3.2 billion US
dollars in foreign investment, according to the mayor, and in
order to get more, it has held a number of trade and investment
fairs and press conferences in Hong Kong, Milan, Tokyo, Bangkok,
and other cities.
</P>
<P>
For seven straight years. the annual Xi'an Ancient Culture and
Art Festival, and Trade and Investment Fair have been organized in
the city. These activities have attracted many people, and large
international companies from 47 countries and regions have opened
businesses in the city, bringing 4.94 billion US dollars in
contracts.
</P>
<P>
Foreign enterprises have been active in electronics,
telecommunications, machine building, and biochemicals and have
exported goods to 104 foreign countries and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
