<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Registers Negative Inflation, Says Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica registered a
negative inflation of 0.4 percent in September, the second in
seven years, said Economy Minister Jose Leon Desanti.
</P>
<P>
This negative inflation is a clear proof of the slowing down of
prices increase of a basket of 264 basic consumer products and
services.
</P>
<P>
But, Gilbert Brown, general secretary of the Rerum Novarum
labor union federation, said that the alleged retraction of the
inflation "are government figures. We feel our pockets emptier
with the high prices index."
</P>
<P>
The accumulated inflation in the first nine months of the year
reached 8.25 percent. Annual inflation, measured between October
of 1996 and September of 1997 is 12 percent, below the 17 percent
registered in the previous 12 months.
</P>
<P>
The government target is to close the year with a 12 percent
inflation for the year.
</P>
<P>
Vice President Rodrigo Oreamuno underscored that the result
shows that the economic policies work well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
