<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Township Enterprises in East China Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Township enterprises in east
China's Zhejiang province have been using a share-holding system,
corporations, new management, and economic responsibility to
improve economic efficiency.
</P>
<P>
About 100 township enterprises now have more than 100 million
yuan (12 million US dollars) in fixed assets each and 400 township
enterprises generate a total of 20 million yuan in annual pre-tax
profit each.
</P>
<P>
Township enterprises had 326.1 billion yuan in sales in the
first half of the year, and earned a total profit of 16.2 billion
yuan, an increase of 19.2 percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Their industrial added value accounted for 63.3 percent of the
province's total by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output and tax revenues of township enterprises in
Taizhou were 93 percent and 89 percent of the city's total,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Clothing in Ningbo, textiles in Shaoxin, leather processing in
Haining, and hardware in Yongkang have all become local
industries, and 624 township enterprises are listed as large and
medium sized enterprises in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
