<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hurricane Kills Over 120 in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, October 9 (Xinhua) -- More than 120 people were
killed today by Hurricane Pauline in Acapulco and other towns on
Mexico's Pacific Coast, said government sources.
</P>
<P>
The hurricane, the strongest in recent memory, swept Acapulco,
a tourist resort in southern Mexico, at a speed of 190 kilometers
per hour and the downpours turned streets into raging rivers.
</P>
<P>
Bodies were seen floating in floodwater and waiting to for
collection, witnesses said.
</P>
<P>
At least 50 people lost their lives and thousands lost their
homes, said a spokesman for the town's fire department.
</P>
<P>
Around 5,000 homeless people had been settled in 13 temporary
camps set up in the town.
</P>
<P>
No tourists were reported among the casualties.
</P>
<P>
Pauline, in its passage across the town, damaged buildings
including hotels, swept away cars, uprooted trees and broke
telephone and power lines.
</P>
<P>
All social activities were brought to a sudden halt with shops
shuttered and schools closed.
</P>
<P>
Governor Rivero had issued an appeal for food, water, medicine,
clothing and construction materials.
</P>
<P>
In Cuajinicuilapa, another town in Guerrero state, five more
bodies were recovered while in Oaxaca state 14 people were found
dead, 15 missing and 4,000 left homeless.
</P>
<P>
Oaxaca state has been declared a disaster zone after being hit
by the hurricane Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971010.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 10 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers are as follows:
</P>
<P>
 People's Daily
</P>
<P>
-- The country's leading newspaper today frontpaged an
editorial on the primary stage of socialism. It says that the
theory of the primary stage of socialism is an essential component
of Deng Xiaoping Theory. The editorial quoted President Jiang
Zemin as saying that China is and will be at the primary stage of
socialism for a long period of time.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng pledged that China will continue efforts to
develop Sino-US economic and trade relations, and noted that the
Chinese government has always assumed a "positive attitude" in
this regard.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with US Commerce Secretary William Daley
yesterday, Li said that the United States is China's key trade
partner, and noted the vast potential for further cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The premier expressed the hope that both sides will study and
supply each other's needs in order to expand trade relations.
</P>
<P>
 Xinhua Daily Telegraph
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, chairman of the Central Military Commission,
has issued an order to put into effect four sets of revised
regulations on interior service, discipline, formation drilling
and garrison concerning the People's Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Original regulations were issued in the early 1990s, while the
new ones better carry out China's military strategy in the new
period and draw in the successful experience in the course of the
army building and reform over the past years, military sources
said.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the new regulations will ensure the absolute
leadership of the Communist Party of China over the army, fully
implement the policies worked out at the just-ended 15th National
Party Congress, and raise the army's combat effectiveness.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Li Peng said yesterday that overall Sino-Italian
relations have witnessed smooth progress in the political,
economic, cultural, educational, scientific and military areas
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties in 1970.
</P>
<P>
Li hoped the development momentum can be maintained when he was
meeting with visiting Italian Defense Minister Beniamino Andreatta.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China's industrial output continued to enjoy a steady growth
in the third quarter this year. The industrial output grew 10.1
percent compared with the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
-- Both spokesmen for the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of
the State Council and the Ministry of Foreign Affairs said
yesterday in Beijing that the maiden policy address made by Tung
Chee-hwa, chief executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, has received widespread favorable comments in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
-- China is striving to take some strategic measures to speed
up the growth of its petroleum sector to satisfy the demand of the
country's sustainable development. As a key move, China is
concentrating on oil exploration to locate more recoverable
reserves. 
</P>
