<HEADLINE> French Motor-Cyclist to Tour World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Gerard Starck, a member of the
French Red Cross, started an ambitious world tour by motorbike
Thursday with a plan of visiting more than 160 Red Cross societies
over 45 months.
</P>
<P>
The 51-year-old has been supported by the Geneva-based
International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies.
</P>
<P>
Starck's world tour will be completed in three stages. In the
first stage from October 1997 to February 1999, he will visit
southern Europe and Africa, travelling over 70,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The following 90,000-kilometer tour will take him through Asia,
Oceania as well as northern and eastern Europe from May 1999 to
July 2000. In the last stage, Starck will have a 40,000-kilometer
tour in the Americas.
</P>
<P>
During the tour, Starck will symbolically link Red Cross and
Red Crescent National Societies around the world with a red ribbon
which he will present to each of the Red Cross and Red Crescent
National Societies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
