<HEADLINE> English Olympic Silver Medallist Killed in Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Atlanta Olympic yachting silver
medallist John Merricks died in a road crash in Italy, Italian
police said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Merricks, 26, won the silver medal in his 470 class dinghy in
the Atlanta Olympics last year with partner Ian Walker.
</P>
<P>
The two men were competing in the European Melges 24
Championships at Punta Ala when the accident happened on
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Merricks was killed instantly. Walker escaped injury but three
of the other six people in the vehicle suffered minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
They were named by police as Anna Hewitt, Andrew Yeomans and
Sacha Nice.
</P>
<P>
Olympic team manager Rod Carr paid tribute to Merricks, who had
been tipped to win gold at the 2000 Olympics in Sydney. 
</P>
