<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Bosnian Serbs to Turn in Indicted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Pentagon urged the Bosnian
Serbs today to turn over the Serbs accused of committing war
crimes during the Bosnian civil war to the war crimes tribunal in
the Hague.
</P>
<P>
The Bosnian Croatians and Muslims have complied with the Dayton
Accord by turning over the indicted, Pentagon spokesman Kenneth
Bacon told a regular briefing, when referring to the hand-over of
ten people by the Croatians to the tribunal.
</P>
<P>
"Most of the non-Serb indicted war criminals have now been
round up, that is the Bosnians and the Croatians," Bacon said.
</P>
<P>
"So it puts more pressure on the Serbs to comply with the terms
of the Dayton Accord, since the Croatians and the Bosnians already
have done that," he added.
</P>
<P>
"I think the lesson is clear: that the international community
is serious about bringing indicted war criminals to justice," he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"And we have been working hard with the formerly warring
parties to convince them to do that. And this is a sign that those
efforts are succeeding," the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
