<DATE_TIME> 1997-10-09 21:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tunisian Government Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, October 9 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian President Zeinul Abidine
Bin Ali today reshuffled the government, with ministers of foreign
and interior affairs, among others, being replaced.
</P>
<P>
But no reason was given for the cabinet shake-up.
</P>
<P>
Saeed Bin Mustafa, currently Tunisia's Ambassador to Rome, was
appointed as the foreign minister, replacing Abderrahim Zouari,
according to Tunisian News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The present Minister of Housing Ali Chaouch has been named
as the Minister of Interior to replace Mohamed Ben Rejeb.
</P>
<P>
Other appointments are Reda Farsheo as Minister of Education,
Hussein Al Shok as Minister of Transport, Salahuddin Beleid as
Minister of Housing, Al Munsif Bin Abdulla as Minister of
Industry, and Sadik Rabah as Minister of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The previous cabinet reshuffle was on January 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
